In Bahonko v Nurses Board of Victoria (No 4) [2007] FCA 1449 ; (2007) 97 ALD 721 , Middleton J considered at [47] and [48] the principles to be applied in exercising the discretion under s 46PO(2) of the HREOC Act and held that the three main matters that need to be taken into account are: (a) The explanation of the delay;
(b) any prejudice to the respondent; and
(c) whether the applicant has an arguable case.
